        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 25 at 1:11PM PDT by NWS Reno NV</headline>
        <description>At 111 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Ebbetts Pass, or 13 miles southwest of Topaz Lake, moving northeast
at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Junction CA 89 And CA 4, Indian Creek Reservoir, Alpine County
Airport, and Markleeville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
